/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  vlle01_waterButanol  --  isothermal flash with `phaseSet VLLE`.

  HONEST-FAILURE TUTORIAL (read README.md).  Water + 1-butanol is the
  classic partially-miscible binary, so a student rightly expects a
  V + Laqueous + Lorganic three-phase split at 373 K, 1.013 bar (above
  the bubble point, so vapour is genuinely present).  It does NOT happen
  here -- and that is the lesson.

  The NRTL parameters in `constant/thermoPackage` are the REAL, cited
  DECHEMA VLE-regressed set (Vol. I/1a p.336, via ChemSep -- see the
  thermoPackage header for the full provenance).  Being a VLE fit, that
  set carries NO liquid-liquid miscibility gap: the VLLE Gibbs-minimiser
  finds the single-liquid optimum, demotes to a TWO-phase V + L result
  (sol.threePhase == false), and the flowsheet emits THREE streams with
  the empty `organic` carrying F = 0.  The surviving liquid is
  butanol-rich (so its `aqueous` label is only a slot name, not a
  physical aqueous phase -- the README spells this out).

  We deliberately keep cited-but-LLE-blind parameters instead of inventing
  numbers to manufacture a gap (Choupo credo: sourced-and-cited, or
  honest-failure-as-lesson -- nothing in between).

  WHAT THIS DEMONSTRATES:

      * the VLE-fit-misses-LLE failure mode, made VISIBLE: a published
        parameter set that is fine for VLE silently has no LL gap;
      * the IsothermalFlash VLLE branch and its honest 2-phase fallback
        (direct Gibbs-energy minimisation, multi-start Nelder-Mead; one
        liquid collapses to beta ~ 0 -> demoted to V+L, announced aloud);
      * the fixed 3-output flowsheet contract for VLLE (always emit V +
        Lalpha + Lbeta; absent phases get F = 0 so the topology is fixed
        regardless of the optimum's regime).

  To actually SEE the gap a student must supply LLE-specific parameters
  (DECHEMA Vol. V LLE Data Collection, Soerensen & Arlt) -- the README
  gives the recipe.  A correctly-split tutorial awaits a curated,
  per-value-cited LLE parameter set.
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

streams
{
    feed
    {
        F            100.0 kmol/h;
        T            373.0 K;
        P            1.013 bar;
        molarComposition  { water 0.50;  nButanol 0.50; }
    }
}

units
(
    {
        name        decanter01;
        type        isothermalFlash;
        in          feed;
        outputs     ( vapor  aqueous  organic );

        operation
        {
            T          373.0 K;
            P          1.013 bar;
            phaseSet   VLLE;
            alphaRich  water;
            betaRich   nButanol;
        }

        compositionTol   1e-5;
        maxOuterIter     200;
    }
);
